{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH85D4D2vDPsjXev4gmn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests pass.\n\n## Fix\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/userService.js`, `getUsers` built its cache key from only the team:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}`;\n```\n\nBut results depend on `opts.includeArchived` too. So when some caller ran `getUsers({ team, includeArchived: true })`, the archived-inclusive list got cached under `users:<team>`. The people picker's own call — `getUsers({ team })` with archived users *not* requested — then hit that same key and got the archived list back. The 60s TTL is why refreshing after a minute (once the entry expires) clears it.\n\n**Change:** Include `includeArchived` in the cache key so the two request shapes don't share a slot:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"archived\" : \"active\"}`;\n```\n\n`npm test` passes. The existing suite only covers `cache.js` directly, so it didn't exercise this path — but the fix is minimal and the key now distinguishes the two variants of the request."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":322,"cache_read_input_tokens":23786,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":322},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2fba79b-7275-4cb3-93f6-f0450bdb13e7","uuid":"6c42e17d-b5ca-41ac-a828-46cedf2f074b","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:48:50.254Z","request_id":"req_011CdH85C1hkN5XdkcniSoYV"}
